about/.title: Who Am I?
about/.body:
About Me
This page tells you a little bit about me. And there is not much to tell, apart from:
My name is m0j0 (for now) and I love Cyber things. I am also a loving Husband/Father/Carer and Tech nerd.
I am currently studying the R60 BSc at the Open University going into my 3rd year. I have had a couple of goes at this but the past 2 yearsâ€¦ Iâ€™ll not bore you.
So far I have completed 8 modules which has gained me a Diploma in HE (Higher Education). This year I am finishing TM352 which is the Level 3 Web/Mobile/Cloud module offered by The Open University.
It only began on October the 5th so early, so far I am enjoying it :) This will lead me up to System Pen-Testing one I look forward too, although have heard conflicting reports.
Completed Modules to date (Oct 24):
Year 1 Modules:
    TM111
    TM112
    TM129
    MU123
Year 2 Modules:
    TT284
    TM257
    TM255
    TM256
Year 3 Modules:
    TM352
    TM359
Anyway HTB?THM/ and the occassional CTF are my practice grounds and the Academy for learnings. I am building these GitBook to reinforce some machines/challenges I have completed so I have to try them again and write better notes and save commands I have learnt.
See you soon (:
Interests

Binary exploitation
Reverse engineering
Crypto vulnerabilities

Tools

pwntools
pwndbg
Ghidra
Burp Suite

This is interesting a SQLite3 DB with:
#!/bin/bash
DB=$1
date_str=$(date +'%d_%b')
7z a -p'H@ckThisP@ssW0rDIfY0uC@n:)' /var/www/backups/${date_str}_db_backup.sqlite3.7z db.sqlite3
cd /var/www/backups/
ls -l --sort=t *.7z > backups_num.tmp
backups_num=$(cat backups_num.tmp | wc -l)
if [[ $backups_num -gt 10 ]]; then
      #backups is more than 10... deleting to oldest backup
      rm $(ls  *.7z --sort=t --color=never | tail -1)
      #oldest backup deleted successfully!
fi
rm backups_num.tmp
